title: 820-00239 Not turning on
message: Liquid-damage. Replaced R5171 and the other bad-looking components in the SMC_LID area. Has 3.4V on SMC_LID now. PPBUS at 13V. No cycling on 5V_S4. I'm attaching some pre-ultrasonic cleaning pictures. I've checked and replaced everything in the corroded areas. Not sure where to go next.

title: 820-00239 Not turning on
message:
Check RTC signals first.
Post _SUS and _S5 voltages and signals from U7800.

title: 820-00239 Not turning on
message:
3V3_S5 is at 3.3V
3V3_SUS is at 0V
PM_SLP_SUS_L is at 0V

PP3V0_G3H is at 3V

title: 820-00239 Not turning on
message:
"PM_SLP_SUS_L is at 0V"
That's the reason 3V3_SUS is missing.

Check RTC signals for PCH.
Does it get 32KHz?

Is PM_BATLOW_L high?

title: 820-00239 Not turning on
message:
I don't have an oscilloscope but I'm measuring .56V on SYSCLK_CLK32K_PCH

PPDCPRTC_PCH is at 1.1V

PCH_SRTCRST_L is at 3V

RTC_RESET_L is at 3V

PM_BATLOW_L is at 3.3V

title: 820-00239 Not turning on
message:
"PPDCPRTC_PCH is at 1.1V"
Appears to be 3V from schematic.
Check/change C1231.
If still the same, bad CPU..

Check also PCH_INTRUDER_L.
